Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: ruby2shoes
Version: 1.09
Summary: low-resource writer's software for screenplays and fiction
Home-page: http://python.org/pypi/ruby2shoes
Author: Ruby Dos Zapatas
Author-email: richardharris@operamail.com
License: GNU General Public License
Description: ruby2shoes combines Emacs and Python to create a sophisticated
        writing environment for screenplay and fiction writers.  Emacs'
        modes are used to create .sp or .fc files.  Spirit, a Python
        application, then archives these files, converts them to text,
        HTML or LaTeX, or prints them in a variety of ways.
        
